deleteDataCollectorText1: When you delete a data collector, all the associated data sources are also deleted and no longer collect information. All the data from the Real Time Display tab is removed, but historical data is still available for the Dashboards tab.
deleteDataCollectorText2: To confirm, enter the name of the data collector you want to delete.
mismatchedDataCollectors: The specified name does not match the selected data collector.
deleteDcButton.tooltip: Only data collectors that are not connected can be deleted.
openLinkToConnector: Open the data collector page in a new tab
dataSourceNotSetupInfo: No plug-ins are enabled for the device. Go to the data collector and enable at least one supported plug-in.
dataSourceWaitingForPluginInfo: The connection with the plug-ins is being established and there is no data transfer yet. Wait for the connection to be established or go to the data collector and make sure that there are no connectivity issues.
dataSourceNotConnectedInfo: The plug-ins cannot communicate with the device and there is no data transfer. Go to the data collector, verify the plug-in settings and the network settings, and fix any connectivity issues.
dataSourceNotAvailableInfo: Cannot communicate with the data collector to retrieve device information. Verify the network settings and fix any connectivity issues.
printerNotSetupInfo: No plug-ins are enabled for the printer. Go to the data collector and enable at least one supported plug-in.
printerNotConnectedInfo: The plug-ins cannot communicate with the printer and there is no data transfer. Go to the data collector, verify the plug-in settings and the network settings, and fix any connectivity issues.
printerNotAvailableInfo: Cannot communicate with the data collector to retrieve printer information. Verify the network settings and fix any connectivity issues.
finisherNotSetupInfo: No plug-ins are enabled for the finisher. Go to the data collector and enable at least one supported plug-in.
finisherNotConnectedInfo: The plug-ins cannot communicate with the finisher and there is no data transfer. Go to the data collector, verify the plug-in settings and the network settings, and fix any connectivity issues.
finisherNotAvailableInfo: Cannot communicate with the data collector to retrieve finisher information. Verify the network settings and fix any connectivity issues.
dcStartup.startupText.one: Start by downloading a data collector client.
dcStartup.startupText.two: Data collector clients enable collection of usage statistics from printers and other data sources.
dcStartup.startupText.three: After the data collector is installed and data sources are added, return to this URL and open the Dashboards tab to view productivity information.

dcInstallers.footerText1: To run RICOH Supervisor Data Collector, your computer must meet these requirements:

dcInstallers.footerText4: A main memory of minimum 4 GB RAM or higher, 64-bit CPU for Windows or Linux, and 15 GB hard disk space available.
